DR. SHIRLEY,So where did this “Tony the Lip” moniker come from?
LIP,Not Tony the Lip. Tony Lip--it’s one word. I got it when I was a kid. My friends said I was the best bullshit artist in the Bronx.
DR. SHIRLEY,Why are you smiling?
LIP,Huh?
LIP,You don’t mind that your friends-- the people closest to you--consider you a liar?
DR. SHIRLEY,"I never said liar, I said bullshit artist."
LIP,What’s the difference?
DR. SHIRLEY,"I don’t lie. I’m just good at, you know, talking people into doin’ things they don’t wanna do. By bullshittin’ ‘em."
LIP,And you’re proud of that?
